	"description": "Hot tips to bring the awesomeness of Visual Studio Code to Vim.\n\nFront-Matter\nI want to start by saying, this is not an editor-shame article. You can use\nwhatever text editor you want. It really doesn’t matter. I’m only writing this\nbecause I found a level of productivity in Vim that I haven’t had in any of the\neditors I used before (Sublime Text, Atom or VSCode).\n\nIf you’ve heard about Vim, and want to try it out, I hope this article can\nprovide a bit of familiarity you’d find from VSCode.\n\nWhy",
